	<div class="posts">
	<a name="83728010">&nbsp;</a><br>
	<a href="http://www.wildetechnologies.com/products_works.html" target="_top">Wilde 1.0 - The Product and How it Works</a><br />There are nice animations here.  I see different levels of detail but not different levels of abstraction here.  I also see that execution is at the component glue level.   I suppose Miser isn't any different than that, so I should not be too cynical.  <br /><br />It appears to depend on the component existing (where is it kept) and for new components, starting with a UML characterization and also providing an implementation that Wilde 1.0 can then integrate.  <br /><br />I have been capturing all of this as a view of integration technology.  It will take digging deeper to see if there is a better way to situate this in the scheme of things.<br>
	<span class="byline">posted by Dennis at <a href="#83728010">Tuesday, October 29, 2002</a></span></div>
<br>
